{"metadata":{"objective":"","lastStepAudioPath":""},"steps":[{"headerText":"This is guided practice 1 b","leftText":"<p>Here is some text.&nbsp;</p><p>Here is some text.&nbsp;</p><p>Here is some text.&nbsp;</p><p>Here is the edit for 1-10-17 test</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","rightText":"<p>Does the box start at the top of the step so that it is a little above the title?</p><p>It should be.&nbsp;&nbsp; See the next step for a picture.</p>","settings":{"showHeader":1,"showAudio":1,"audioPath":"","hideRightPanel":0,"showNext":1,"delayStep":"0","delayRight":"0","showRFB":1}},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"showRuler":0,"showRFB":1},"leftText":"<p>A <strong>sentence fragment</strong> is an incomplete sentence.&nbsp; It may be missing either a <strong>subject</strong> (tells who or what is performing the action the sentence is describing) or a <strong>verb</strong> (tells what the subject is doing or state of being of the subject).<br /><br />The fragment might also be a <strong>dependent clause</strong> (cannot stand on its own) with no <strong>independent clause</strong> (can stand on its own as a complete sentence) to complete the idea.</p>","rightText":null,"headerText":"Recognizing a sentence fragment"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"showRuler":0,"showRFB":1},"leftText":"<p>Picture from prod of how it looks:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p>","rightText":null}],"overviewHeader":"Overview","inputData":{},"rightFloatText":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><p>How do I look?&nbsp;&nbsp; I should be aligned with the top of the step--I actually start above the title.</p><p>2</p><p>2</p><p>2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table>"}
